{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17492578","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17492578"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T06:36:38+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T06:36:38+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1104"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"1104","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/1104"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.19,0.07,0.01,0,0.73]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"1104"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"27189"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"1104","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/1104"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question","status":"accepted","createdAt":"2019-11-15T21:27:39+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-05-20T14:30:19+09:30","updatedAction":"commented","acceptedAt":"2021-07-20T11:34:58+09:30","editorNotifiedAt":null,"feedbackAt":"2025-09-23 20:05:58"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1104"}},"updatedBy":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"738"}},"author":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"9"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"14116"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"28"},{"type":"tags","id":"31"},{"type":"tags","id":"66"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"377"},{"type":"tags","id":"4174"},{"type":"tags","id":"8088"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"3237"},{"type":"contributions","id":"16656"}]},"lastContribution":{"data":null},"lastRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"14116"}},"lastActivity":{"data":null},"lastFeedback":{"data":null}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"27189","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/27189"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 52-year-old woman presents with a two week history of increasing breathlessness. She also reports a chest wall lesion (Image) that she has been too embarrassed to seek advice on for the last year. There is dullness to percussion in the right base, with reduced breath sounds and shifting dullness on abdominal examination.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most appropriate plan of management?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Mastectomy","Radiotherapy","Tamoxifen","Letrozole","Palliative care"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis unfortunate woman has a invasive, locally advanced carcinoma of the breast. The related clinical signs suggest a malignant pleural effusion and ascites. Both of these undoubtedly represent metastatic spread of this tumour. The most dignified approach to her management must be \u003Cstrong\u003Epalliative care\u003C/strong\u003E. No other treatment is going to have any influence on the disease process.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003ELower stage breast cancer can be treated with a \u003Cstrong\u003Emastectomy\u003C/strong\u003E based on specific characteristics such as size and type, and potential low grade tumours can be treated with breast-conserving surgery. \u003Cstrong\u003ERadiotherapy\u003C/strong\u003E is often used to remove any residual disease, especially in breast-conserving surgery. \u003Cstrong\u003ETamoxifen\u003C/strong\u003E is a selective oestrogen receptor modular (SERM) is used to treat oestrogen-receptor positive breast cancer. \u003Cstrong\u003ELetrozole\u003C/strong\u003E is an aromatase inhibitor used for breast cancer treatment in post-menopausal women. In some circumstances, some of these treatment options may be used with palliative care but even then the average survival is a few months.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Ulcerative breast cancer has a very poor prognosis.","Metastatic cancer is best treated with a holistic palliative care approach."],"references":["Vempati P, Knoll MA, Dharmarajan K, Green S, Tiersten A, Bakst RL. Palliation of Ulcerative Breast Lesions with Radiation. Anticancer res. 2016; 36(9): 4701-5."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"14116"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1104"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"16890"}]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"media","id":"16890","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/16890"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/535b498f-8e12-46eb-810c-4a77ad42c7e8.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/535b498f-8e12-46eb-810c-4a77ad42c7e8.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":800,"height":600}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"14116","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/14116"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2022-08-27T20:49:04+09:30","updatedAt":"2024-10-07T08:56:13+10:30","number":6,"notes":"","plagiarismCheckedAt":"2024-10-07T08:55:43+10:30","plagiarismScore":0,"plagiarismReportUrl":"https://emedici-copyleaks.syd1.digitaloceanspaces.com/plagiarism-report-1104-6.pdf?X-Amz-Content-Sha256=UNSIGNED-PAYLOAD\u0026X-Amz-Algorithm=AWS4-HMAC-SHA256\u0026X-Amz-Credential=DO00QAKVE68N83EBLT2J%2F20250928%2Fsyd1%2Fs3%2Faws4_request\u0026X-Amz-Date=20250928T210639Z\u0026X-Amz-SignedHeaders=host\u0026X-Amz-Expires=601200\u0026X-Amz-Signature=139cdd02ad7c6fd52a07efade16d5eaf77b90ea60f3659b5e97c8deb2e305ab1"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"1104"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"27189"}},"author":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"738"}},"generation":{"data":null}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"28","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/28"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc95","name":"Palliative Care","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"crea